list.name: Default
list.comment: Created testing capabilities added multiple test scripts fixed bug with waterUsageGraph added error handling for Item, group and eventcall

task.summary: Default task
added Gitignore

added ItemGroup and object that links Items and Groups
Now when getting an item this class will query for groups on top of the item itself but leave the groups items empty to avoid looping. visa versa for getting a group

added EventCall This object has a json field. This is a stringified version of request.data This object is used to temporarily store data that the homelynk will supply.
runs at /event_call contains - id - json - timestamp
Removed unnecessary lines

Added Day, Graph, Hour and Week
These are all used to find date regarding graphs.
Next step: When a Day or Hour is not found in the database an Insufficient_data_event should be thrown.

Added the processor day and hour objects are now generated when the data is being processed and they don't exist yet.
Created a dummy processor that takes the average temperature of all the temperature events during a specific hour

EventCallResource - GET
bug fix
Is_module added to group. Items are online allowed to be in one module.
Changed endpoints to starting with /api
Changed DB Changed migrations Wrote Seeder minor changes to models
use null values for hour.value if there are no events
allowed null values for hour.value
null values are now allowed for hour.value
added optional starting and ending date timestamps for graph.get endpoint
proper week assesment
fixed bug where starting date had to be the precise moment the week started. Now this can be any timestamp within the week

added last_usage to item. This contains information about the last event that belongs to the item. added CommandResource this is a resource for the api endpoint /api/item/<item_id>/command/<value> This endpoint will be changed later on, but for now it is able to send a http request to Homelynk's endpoint
Fixed bug

redefined table names because of reserved keywords in SQL Created test_app which is a test version of app.py. This resets the database everytime it is run. Created test_manage.py with the run_test command so that tests can be run.
Increased testing functionality Created tests for items and groups Fixed some bugs in items and groups
Created testing capabilities added multiple test scripts fixed bug with waterUsageGraph added error handling for Item, group and eventcall
